snippet.textDisplay: He did not make a "Chicago style" deep dish.  Different dough (should be almost pie dough like), sliced mozzarella, then plain tomato sauce (best you can buy or make).  Bake in much more substantial pan, using some butter to line the pan before the dough.  NY style vs Chicago, very different meals.  One is a quick street snack (one of the best in the world), the other is a sit down and enjoy the company of others dinner.  They both have merits, I like them both for different reasons.
